commit.message:
Don't hardcode libpng version in macOS CI

libpng is provided by brew and updated independently.
Until fully switching to CMake or pkgconfig, replace the hardcoded version number with the libpng version reported by pkg-config.
Fixes the build error on macOS CI.

Disable continue-on-error on macOS CI

Continue-on-error breaks propagating the "failed" state from the job to the macOS workflow.
Update all GH checkout steps

Provide lld for Ubuntu Intel Clang CI

Fixes failing cmake configuration step.
Performance: Use float multiplication instead of division

Image crop: Use goto

Using goto instead of the `match` helper variable makes the code easier to read
and has a tiny performance benefit.

Image crop: Avoid unnecessary loop through corners

In the horizontal crop, we do not need to check the corners that were already
removed in the preceding vertical crop.

WebPDecodeARGB()'s return should be WebPFree()ed. (#836)

According to Google's spec, "The code that calls any of these functions
must delete the data buffer (uint8_t*) returned by these functions with 
WebPFree()."

Using free() instead was causing heap corruption crashes for me (Windows 
MSVC 2019 compile)

commit.message:
Fix php/php-src#10614: Consistently set saveAlphaFlag

The non-square degree rotation cases, and the 0 degree rotation case all
set saveAlphaFlag to 1. But the other special cases for 90, 180, or 270
degrees don't. This results in losing the alpha channel, and in
particular if an image is black on a transparent background, in a
full-black image. Fix it by setting the saveAlphaFlag.

configure: use m4_tolower helper

This is new in autoconf-2.69 and lets us kill off some boilerplate
in our various library tests.

configure: require autoconf-2.69

This was released in 2012, and only developers really need it, so
bump the requirement.  This will let us use some newer features
that aren't available in 2.64.

configure: add log when we check config scripts

This should make it more obvious when we aren't probing for the libs
and headers directy ourselves.

Closes #841.
